PRESS DIGEST - Norway - Sept 9 . Following are some of the leading stories in Norwegian papers this morning : AFTENPOSTEN - Local Government Minister Gunnar Berge believes that the unemployment rate will drop below four percent next year . - The state pollution agency wants to ban the dumping of old ships at sea because steel and other parts in the hulls can be recycled . No such ban however is proposed against dumping decommissioned oil platforms . DAGENS NAERINGSLIV - Prime Minister Gro Harlem Brundtland says Norwegian industry has come to accept that the state has a role to play in private business . - Sysdeco , the Norwegian software company , was not aware that Citco Global Custody was its main shareholder until the Morgan Grenfell affair came to light . - Subsidised modems with an Internet subscription are selling like crazy . 
